5
00:02:35,058 --> 00:02:36,447
先生 Savage先生
Mr. Savage, sir,

6
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:37,730
我不知道(您要出门) 先生
I didn't know, sir.

7
00:02:37,807 --> 00:02:39,053
我不知道
Sir, I didn't know.

8
00:02:39,131 --> 00:02:40,936
没关系的 Benson
It's all right, Benson,

9
00:02:41,011 --> 00:02:42,922
临时决定的
last minute decision.

10
00:03:29,231 --> 00:03:31,628
哦 你在这儿啊
Oh, there you are.

11
00:03:31,702 --> 00:03:34,277
早上好 Adelaide
Adelaide, good morning.

12
00:03:37,238 --> 00:03:38,733
Victor去哪啦?
Where has Victor gone?

13
00:03:38,804 --> 00:03:40,014
Victor?
Victor?

14
00:03:40,093 --> 00:03:41,232
Victor
Victor.

15
00:03:41,312 --> 00:03:43,294
不要装作你不知道
Please don't pretend you are ignorant of where he is.

16
00:03:43,365 --> 00:03:44,955
我是我表弟的监护人么?
Am I my cousin's keeper?

17
00:03:45,037 --> 00:03:47,503
要是你告诉我他去哪了 我会很感激你的
I shall be obliged that you would tell me where he has gone.

18
00:03:47,539 --> 00:03:49,519
我知道他要去干什么
I know what he's gone to do.

19
00:03:49,598 --> 00:03:50,527
但他去了哪里呢?
Where has he gone?

20
00:03:50,563 --> 00:03:52,413
你应该比我更容易知道这一点吧 亲爱的
You have the advantage of me, my dear.

21
00:03:52,487 --> 00:03:55,886
我还想着今早和他 去看看家里的农场呢
I was expecting to walk over to home farm with him this morning.

22
00:03:55,923 --> 00:03:57,846
你就一点不同情我们么?
Have you no pity for us?

23
00:03:57,918 --> 00:04:01,086
是你怂恿他过这种噩梦似的生活
You encouraged him into this nightmarish life.

24
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:06,721
我"同情"你
I pity for you

25
00:04:06,797 --> 00:04:08,077
和你可爱的孩子们
at Somerleigh House

26
00:04:08,154 --> 00:04:09,293
在Somerleigh庄园
with your lovely children,

27
00:04:09,372 --> 00:04:10,725
你们彼此之间相亲相爱
the love you have for each other.

28
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:12,547
他到底去哪里了?
Where has he gone?

29
00:04:13,620 --> 00:04:15,733
看得出我不受欢迎
I can see I am unwelcome,

30
00:04:15,814 --> 00:04:18,840
恐怕只是因为些不经意的错误
some unwitting fault I fear.

31
00:04:18,912 --> 00:04:20,466
我应该回城里去
I shall return to town

32
00:04:20,549 --> 00:04:22,697
好给你留个清净
and leave you in peace.

33
00:04:31,585 --> 00:04:33,372
-Hudson太太 -华生医生
-Oh, Mrs. Hudson. -Oh, Dr. Watson.

34
00:04:33,409 --> 00:04:35,549
我们都很想你
We have been missing you.

35
00:04:35,624 --> 00:04:36,977
噢 是么 才10天没见
Oh yeah, only another 10 days.

36
00:04:37,051 --> 00:04:38,925
是啊
Yes.

37
00:04:40,289 --> 00:04:42,021
早上好 福尔摩斯
Morning, Holmes.

38
00:04:44,745 --> 00:04:48,222
别要我评论你的新领带
Don't ask me to comment on your new tie.

39
00:04:51,882 --> 00:04:53,995
真够无情的 福尔摩斯
Quite heartless, Holmes.

40
00:04:59,334 --> 00:05:03,298
那个女人无疑是想到这来
That woman is undoubtedly coming here.

41
00:05:03,372 --> 00:05:04,725
她一直盯著这扇窗户
She's been staring up at this window

42
00:05:04,799 --> 00:05:05,974
已经有三分钟了
for the past three minutes.

43
00:05:06,052 --> 00:05:08,450
我真希望她能下定决心
Oh, I do wish she'd make up her mind.

44
00:05:08,524 --> 00:05:12,072
我会让Hudson太太给她多加只杯子的
I could ask Mrs. Hudson to bring up an extra cup.

45
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:13,498
很漂亮 不是么?
Handsome, isn't she?

46
00:05:13,573 --> 00:05:14,551
谁?
Who?

47
00:05:16,496 --> 00:05:18,335
一定是什么重要的事
It must be something of importance

48
00:05:18,412 --> 00:05:21,746
才让她犹豫了这么久
to make her hesitate so long,

49
00:05:21,824 --> 00:05:23,391
一个委托人?
A client?

50
00:05:49,990 --> 00:05:52,043
还好么 Polly?
Alright, Polly?

51
00:05:52,113 --> 00:05:53,810
真是个可人儿
There's a good girl.

52
00:06:08,198 --> 00:06:11,426
Savage先生 我是John Gedgrave
Mr. Savage, John Gedgrave.

53
00:06:11,506 --> 00:06:12,950
你怎么才来啊?
Where the devil have you been?

54
00:06:14,117 --> 00:06:17,344
先生 先预付2镑
Two pounds, Mr. Savage, in advance

55
00:06:17,424 --> 00:06:19,049
事成之后再付3镑
and three for the establishment,

56
00:06:19,130 --> 00:06:20,863
一共是5英镑
five in total.

57
00:06:20,940 --> 00:06:22,079
希望能值这个价
Hope it's worth it.

58
00:06:22,159 --> 00:06:25,281
您用的匿名
Oh, anonymous was the word you used.

59
00:06:25,363 --> 00:06:26,893
我们去的这地方
Where we're going is as anonymous

60
00:06:26,964 --> 00:06:28,517
也不可能被人发现的
as you'll ever find.

61
00:06:28,601 --> 00:06:30,095
每个小隔间
Every compartment

62
00:06:30,166 --> 00:06:31,900
都还有帘子挡著
has a curtain even.

63
00:06:31,976 --> 00:06:33,115
没人会看到您的
No one will see you,

64
00:06:33,195 --> 00:06:34,476
哦 上帝啊
oh good Lord,

65
00:06:34,553 --> 00:06:37,260
您没都带着吧 是不是?
you're not taking these with you, are you?

66
00:06:37,338 --> 00:06:38,310
不用带着?
No?

67
00:06:38,383 --> 00:06:40,531
哦 不 当然不用
Oh, no, no, no, no.

68
00:06:40,612 --> 00:06:42,165
或许应该把它们撕碎了
May as well tear them up

69
00:06:42,248 --> 00:06:45,024
扔到泰晤士河里
and drop them in the Thames.

70
00:06:45,102 --> 00:06:46,419
四十镑
Forty pounds,

71
00:06:46,495 --> 00:06:48,892
我会给您开张收据的
I'll give you a receipt.

72
00:06:54,015 --> 00:06:54,990
福尔摩斯!
Holmes!

73
00:07:00,213 --> 00:07:02,087
应该是我们漂亮的客人
That will be our fair visitor.

74
00:07:09,752 --> 00:07:11,138
请坐吧
Please, do sit down.

75
00:07:42,025 --> 00:07:43,450
Gedgrave 这张收据
This receipt Gedgrave.

76
00:07:43,524 --> 00:07:44,287
怎么啦?
What about it?

77
00:07:44,359 --> 00:07:45,778
你在玩什么把戏?
What are you playing at?

78
00:07:45,856 --> 00:07:47,102
签的名是Carter
You signed it Carter.

79
00:07:47,179 --> 00:07:48,947
您不会是希望我在做这类事情的时候
You don't expect me to use my real name

80
00:07:49,025 --> 00:07:51,007
还要用我的真名吧?
doing this sort of work, do you?

81
00:07:51,078 --> 00:07:53,155
Carter就是我的真名
Carter's my real name.

82
00:07:53,236 --> 00:07:55,598
我本来可以随便写个名字
I could have signed anything

83
00:07:55,675 --> 00:08:00,825
我信任您才用真名的 Savage先生
but I entrusted you with my real name, Mr. Savage.

84
00:08:00,896 --> 00:08:03,674
您就别再抱怨了
Please don't complain.

85
00:08:15,101 --> 00:08:17,011
我需要您的帮助
I need your help.

86
00:08:19,871 --> 00:08:21,604
我是...
I am...

87
00:08:22,726 --> 00:08:24,185
您在这里所说的一切
Anything you say here will of course

88
00:08:24,258 --> 00:08:25,894
我们都会严格的保守秘密
be treated in the strictest confidence.

89
00:08:26,068 --> 00:08:29,305
我们还替国王们保守着秘密呢 夫人
We have kept the secrets of kings, madam.

90
00:08:31,082 --> 00:08:33,621
我...
I...

91
00:08:33,692 --> 00:08:36,267
我丈夫...
My husband...

92
00:09:10,144 --> 00:09:12,292
我丈夫是个金融家
My husband is a financier.

93
00:09:12,371 --> 00:09:15,006
您一定听过牛津伦巴德银行吧?
You have heard of the Oxford and Lombard Bank?

94
00:09:15,088 --> 00:09:16,749
是的
Yes.

95
00:09:16,828 --> 00:09:19,783
Conyers家族是其主要股东
The chief shareholders are the Conyers?

96
00:09:19,858 --> 00:09:21,935
我丈夫的母亲就属于这一家族
My husband's family on his mother's side.

97
00:09:22,016 --> 00:09:24,484
我丈夫是主要董事之一
He is one of the directors.

98
00:09:24,559 --> 00:09:28,665
他完全胜任这个工作
The job is well within his powers, only...

99
00:09:28,736 --> 00:09:32,901
但他发现这工作越来越令人厌烦
Victor has found the work increasingly irksome.

100
00:09:32,983 --> 00:09:35,939
他怀抱着一种志向
He entertains an ambition, you see,

101
00:09:36,012 --> 00:09:38,788
虽然家里人都无法理解
which none of his family would begin to understand.

102
00:09:38,868 --> 00:09:40,921
什么志向?
What is that?

103
00:09:40,991 --> 00:09:43,106
他想成为一个诗人
He wishes to be a poet.

104
00:09:48,268 --> 00:09:49,503
他开始相信
He's come to believe

105
00:09:49,540 --> 00:09:51,812
吸食鸦片能获得灵感
that opium heightens his powers,

106
00:09:51,888 --> 00:09:54,959
让他的感觉更敏锐
intensifies the evidence of his senses.

107
00:10:17,964 --> 00:10:19,697
这可能能起到临时的作用
This may be so temporarily,

108
00:10:19,775 --> 00:10:20,794
但我想您肯定知道
but as I'm sure you know

109
00:10:20,831 --> 00:10:22,592
只有在最开始几次吸食时
the effect only survives

110
00:10:22,665 --> 00:10:24,017
才有这种效果
the first few times the drug is taken.

111
00:10:24,092 --> 00:10:25,860
是这样么?
That is so, is it not?

112
00:10:25,937 --> 00:10:27,562
是的 完全正确
Oh, yes, indeed.

113
00:10:27,644 --> 00:10:29,102
接下来很快就会上瘾
Addiction quickly follows,

114
00:10:29,175 --> 00:10:30,564
越来越频繁
very often for life.

115
00:10:30,638 --> 00:10:34,124
这种恶魔般的物质 很快就只会使人沉醉其中
The infernal substance soon offers the addict nothing

116
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:37,977
除了在无法吸食时 感到难以忍受以外别无他用
except relief from the terrible effects of its absence.

117
00:10:39,689 --> 00:10:43,296
我相信Victor马上就要成瘾了
I believe Victor stands on the threshold of addiction.

118
00:10:44,007 --> 00:10:45,358
他今早留给我一张便条
He left a note for me this morning

119
00:10:45,395 --> 00:10:47,951
似乎他明白自己处在何种危险之中
which suggests he knows what danger he's in.

120
00:10:49,090 --> 00:10:50,619
您要走了么?
You are going?

121
00:10:50,692 --> 00:10:53,685
很清楚 在这件事情上 华生医生才是您应该去咨询的人
Well clearly Dr. Watson is the person to consult for the matter.

122
00:10:53,722 --> 00:10:54,800
不 福尔摩斯先生 不是的
No, Mr. Holmes, no,

123
00:10:54,837 --> 00:10:56,846
不光是这些
there is much more to it then that.

124
00:10:57,793 --> 00:11:00,712
有一位Culverton Smith先生
There is Mr. Culverton Smith.

125
00:11:00,787 --> 00:11:01,797
Culverton Smith?
Culverton Smith?

126
00:11:02,060 --> 00:11:03,288
Victor的表兄
Victor's cousin.

127
00:11:04,514 --> 00:11:06,768
他肯定是起了什么坏的影响
He's a malign influence.

128
00:11:06,846 --> 00:11:09,694
是他把Victor逼到这份上的
I am sure he's driven Victor to this

129
00:11:09,770 --> 00:11:13,520
我确信他这么做另有目的
and I am certain he's done it for his own ends.

130
00:11:31,671 --> 00:11:33,166
福尔摩斯?
Holmes?

131
00:11:34,803 --> 00:11:36,773
马车就停在街角
The cab's on the corner.

132
00:11:39,573 --> 00:11:41,970
我希望这次不是白费力气
I do hope this is not a wild goose chase.

133
00:11:42,044 --> 00:11:43,468
怎么可能呢?
How can it be?

134
00:11:43,542 --> 00:11:44,811
好吧
Well,

135
00:11:47,231 --> 00:11:50,356
我想那个漂亮姑娘把你 迷的晕头转向 谢谢
I think you've had your head turned by a pretty woman, thank you.

136
00:11:50,748 --> 00:11:52,622
对了 关于Culverton Smith 有什么情况?
Oh yes, what about Culverton Smith?

137
00:11:52,698 --> 00:11:53,759
我调查过他了
I looked him up.

138
00:11:53,796 --> 00:11:56,558
Culverton Smith在东方的时候
Culverton Smith did some important medical work

139
00:11:56,631 --> 00:11:58,185
从事过重要的医学工作
while he was in the east.

140
00:11:58,268 --> 00:12:00,143
他拓宽了科学的领域
He pushed back the boundaries of science.

141
00:12:00,217 --> 00:12:06,761
但是 他却不得不自费发表他的发现
However, he was obliged to publish his findingsat his own expense.

142
00:12:08,226 --> 00:12:09,262
为什么?
Why?

143
00:12:10,245 --> 00:12:11,722
他只是个业余爱好者
He's an amateur

144
00:12:12,752 --> 00:12:15,303
那些专家们又很嫉妒
and the professionals are jealous.

145
00:12:15,467 --> 00:12:18,108
我明白为什么他使你感兴趣了
Well I can see why he interests you.

146
00:12:29,115 --> 00:12:32,343
你那些神秘的客人
Ah, your mystery guests.

147
00:12:32,422 --> 00:12:34,119
他们都是谁?
Who are they?

148
00:12:34,198 --> 00:12:37,995
我可不愿意让Carnac上校 成为唯一的名人
I couldn't let Colonel Carnac be the only celebrity.

149
00:12:38,307 --> 00:12:41,764
我不是因为他有名才请他的 亲爱的
I don't want him at our table because he's a celebrity, my darling.

150
00:12:41,801 --> 00:12:43,910
纯粹是因为他有钱
It's just that he's horribly rich,

151
00:12:43,980 --> 00:12:45,570
或者说他妻子非常有钱
or rather his wife is,

152
00:12:45,653 --> 00:12:49,296
他们都把钱存在牛津伦巴德银行
and they bank with the Oxford and Lombard.

153
00:12:49,378 --> 00:12:52,673
我个人觉得没有比 在餐桌上猎取奇闻异事更糟的了
Personally I can't think of anything worse then hunting stories all through dinner.

154
00:12:52,710 --> 00:12:54,079
我也这么觉得
Nor I.

155
00:12:54,321 --> 00:12:58,719
所以我说服一位很有趣的猎人 也来加入我们
So I've persuaded a rather more interesting hunter to join us.

156
00:12:59,473 --> 00:13:02,842
是谁? 不要捉弄我 Addy
Who is it? Don't tease, Addy.

157
00:13:04,557 --> 00:13:07,110
歇洛克 福尔摩斯
Sherlock Holmes.

158
00:13:07,147 --> 00:13:10,597
要我说 这可真是出乎意料
I say, that is something of a coup,

159
00:13:10,754 --> 00:13:12,178
好极了
well done.

160
00:13:13,610 --> 00:13:16,216
看 Culverton Smith也来了
Oh look, Culverton Smith's here too.

161
00:13:16,882 --> 00:13:19,850
真高兴你又能邀请他 Addy 我亲爱的
I'm so glad you felt able to invite him again, Addy darling.

162
00:13:20,537 --> 00:13:21,683
看看他
Look at him.

163
00:13:22,591 --> 00:13:24,776
大家都会觉得Somerleigh是他的
Anyone would think Somerleigh was his.

164
00:13:25,655 --> 00:13:27,407
我很不喜欢这样
I do dislike it.

165
00:13:41,113 --> 00:13:42,666
-歇洛克 福尔摩斯先生? -是的
-Mr. Sherlock Holmes? -Yes.

166
00:13:42,704 --> 00:13:44,143
我是Culverton Smith
Culverton Smith.

167
00:13:44,179 --> 00:13:47,410
Adelaide告诉我有一位 令人惊喜的客人
Dear Adelaide promised me a surprise guest.

168
00:13:47,485 --> 00:13:50,455
我还担心是因为哗众取宠而出名的人呢
I feared it might be somebody who was famous for being famous.

169
00:13:50,492 --> 00:13:53,525
我没有料到 是您这种级别的
Someone of your distinction I had not expected at all.

170
00:13:53,562 --> 00:13:55,071
我当然没有你出名
Nor I one of yours.

171
00:13:55,144 --> 00:13:56,471
我?
Mine?

172
00:13:57,036 --> 00:13:59,907
我没权要求这种待遇 福尔摩斯先生
I make no claims to distinction, Mr. Holmes.

173
00:13:59,984 --> 00:14:02,096
您过谦了
You are too modest.

174
00:14:02,177 --> 00:14:07,420
你写的关于苏门答腊和洪水热的 病理学报告是一部杰作
Your account of the pathology of the Sumatra and River Fever is a masterpiece.

175
00:14:07,503 --> 00:14:08,570
谢谢
Thank you,

176
00:14:08,608 --> 00:14:10,249
谢谢
thank you.

177
00:14:10,741 --> 00:14:12,421
当然 要让诱饵发挥作用
For a lure to work, of course,

178
00:14:12,459 --> 00:14:14,200
得让动物相信这是安全的
you have to make the animal believe it's safe.

179
00:14:14,237 --> 00:14:16,540
这样就好了
Now that's all very well.

180
00:14:16,729 --> 00:14:20,244
但是 动物们对于危险总是很敏感
The animals involved, however, have a highly developed sense of danger.

181
00:14:20,281 --> 00:14:24,045
我想福尔摩斯先生对危险也很敏感 是吗 福尔摩斯先生?
I'm sure Mr. Holmes must have that sense, do you Mr. Holmes?

182
00:14:24,082 --> 00:14:26,842
是的 我看得出来
Yes, I see it.

183
00:14:26,879 --> 00:14:29,847
那么 你是说侦探
Yes, you mean that the detective

184
00:14:29,925 --> 00:14:30,898
可以说是在
could be said to move

185
00:14:30,935 --> 00:14:33,316
食肉动物和牺牲品的世界里活动
in a world of predators and victims.

186
00:14:33,353 --> 00:14:34,691
我们都是这样的 上校
Oh, we all do that Colonel.

187
00:14:34,729 --> 00:14:37,625
即使是最不起眼的家庭事务律师
Even humble family solicitors.

188
00:14:38,942 --> 00:14:41,892
是的 那你给自己树了不少敌吧 福尔摩斯先生
Yes, and you would have enemies, Mr. Holmes,

189
00:14:41,928 --> 00:14:42,653
你就没有敌人么?
would you not?

190
00:14:42,691 --> 00:14:45,936
对了 我敢说要是
Yes, yes, it would take something I dare say

191
00:14:45,972 --> 00:14:47,845
有人想引福尔摩斯先生上钩然后对付他
to bring Mr. Holmes onto a lure

192
00:14:47,883 --> 00:14:49,918
肯定要花很多工夫
and dispatch him.

193
00:14:50,152 --> 00:14:52,731
需要仔细研究他的习惯
It would take careful study of his habits

194
00:14:52,768 --> 00:14:55,810
在暗处发动袭击
and half-light shot or worse.

195
00:14:56,106 --> 00:14:58,192
必要时甚至要跟踪他
It might even be necessary to follow him

196
00:14:58,229 --> 00:15:00,967
一直追到他的老窝里去
up to his lair even.

197
00:15:01,004 --> 00:15:04,180
Bertram 安静点
Bertram, be quiet.

198
00:15:24,063 --> 00:15:26,297
您没有怎么吃东西 福尔摩斯先生
You're not eating, Mr. Holmes.

199
00:15:28,101 --> 00:15:30,689
有这么多东西要观察
With so much to observe,

200
00:15:31,061 --> 00:15:33,350
吃就是次要的了
food becomes of secondary importance.

201
00:15:33,387 --> 00:15:35,967
您都观察出了些什么?
What have you observed so far?

202
00:15:36,318 --> 00:15:37,639
勇气
Courage,

203
00:15:39,158 --> 00:15:40,786
燥热
fever,

204
00:15:41,297 --> 00:15:42,617
贪婪
gluttony,

205
00:15:43,350 --> 00:15:45,052
愤怒
acute irritation,

206
00:15:46,171 --> 00:15:47,542
嫉妒
envy,

207
00:15:48,851 --> 00:15:50,177
机智
wit, intelligence,

208
00:15:50,214 --> 00:15:54,013
我是说都是些在英格兰所有大庄园里
I mean just the usual vices and virtues

209
00:15:54,050 --> 00:15:56,807
常见的恶性和美德
with any large English country house.

210
00:15:57,451 --> 00:15:59,754
真是好极了
This is very good.

211
00:16:08,174 --> 00:16:09,459
你们知道
Do you know the game

212
00:16:10,525 --> 00:16:11,792
"推硬币"的游戏么?
of "shove ha'penny?"

213
00:16:11,828 --> 00:16:14,229
这个跟那个很像
Well it's similar.

214
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:18,669
我把它叫做"地毯滑冰"
I call this one "Rug skatery".

215
00:16:18,723 --> 00:16:20,780
我那些把赌博当一回事的朋友
My more serious gambling friends,

216
00:16:20,817 --> 00:16:23,479
就是那些股票经纪人
the stock broking fraternity that is to say,

217
00:16:23,516 --> 00:16:25,377
因为把这游戏介绍到自己的居所
have introduced it to their establishments

218
00:16:25,414 --> 00:16:27,406
而惹得妻子们非常生气
to the fury of their wives.

219
00:16:27,443 --> 00:16:29,169
但是大家都同意
It is agreed, however,

220
00:16:29,206 --> 00:16:32,891
论其可靠性来 Somerleigh是最好的
that the authentic Somerleigh version is best.

221
00:16:36,863 --> 00:16:38,642
她压根儿不穿那些东西
And she never wore them at all.

222
00:16:41,214 --> 00:16:44,367
要是我们不鼓动他们去玩那个愚蠢的游戏 男人们会感到苦恼么?
Will the men be mortified if we don't cheer them on at their silly game?

223
00:16:44,404 --> 00:16:45,900
我敢说他们会的
I dare say they will.

224
00:16:46,203 --> 00:16:48,623
这都快成个反面的理由了
It's almost a reason for not doing it.

225
00:16:50,483 --> 00:16:52,750
还不是为了和睦
But for the sake of harmony

226
00:16:52,770 --> 00:16:55,040
我们才迁就这些大孩子
We indulge little boys.

227
00:17:08,231 --> 00:17:10,951
主人又一次超过了大家的预测
Our host has again out jumped all estimates.

228
00:17:11,684 --> 00:17:14,732
-所以律师压对了 -谢谢
-So the lawyer takes the pot. -Thank you.

229
00:17:14,768 --> 00:17:16,084
干得好 Charles
Well done, Charles,

230
00:17:16,210 --> 00:17:17,655
现在该我了
my turn now.

231
00:17:20,346 --> 00:17:22,089
先生们 咱们来赌一把吧
<i>Faites vos jeux, gentlemen</i>

232
00:17:22,259 --> 00:17:25,428
我该把你们最后一次的预测减半
I should halve your estimates of last time.

233
00:17:41,724 --> 00:17:43,012
-妈妈 -没事的
-Mama. -It's quite all right.

234
00:17:43,049 --> 00:17:45,085
我家的孩子也一样
My children do that too.

235
00:17:47,956 --> 00:17:49,035
妈妈
Mama.

236
00:17:56,695 --> 00:17:58,774
爸爸他怎么啦?
What is wrong with papa?

237
00:18:00,046 --> 00:18:01,341
他抱着我的时候
When he hugged me

238
00:18:01,377 --> 00:18:03,395
我觉得很恐怖
he felt horrid.

239
00:18:03,984 --> 00:18:06,629
他浑身冰冷 还在发抖
He felt all cold and shivery.

240
00:18:08,062 --> 00:18:10,412
你想说什么 宝贝?
What do you mean by that, darling?

241
00:18:10,449 --> 00:18:13,002
好像他就快要死了
He felt as if he was dead.

242
00:18:18,243 --> 00:18:19,653
别说傻话了
Oh don't be silly.

243
00:20:28,207 --> 00:20:29,761
医生!
Doctor!

244
00:21:06,682 --> 00:21:08,200
Smith
Smith.

245
00:21:10,059 --> 00:21:11,684
可怜的家伙
Poor fellow.

246
00:21:11,765 --> 00:21:14,507
我没能帮到他 福尔摩斯先生
I could do nothing for him, Mr. Holmes,

247
00:21:14,586 --> 00:21:17,647
连我也没帮得到他
not even I.

248
00:21:17,719 --> 00:21:19,702
护士也在尽力照顾
The nursing was all right, too,

249
00:21:19,772 --> 00:21:21,885
真是一出悲剧
a tragic business.

250
00:21:21,966 --> 00:21:24,564
有一件事 您能帮助我么?
Will you satisfy me upon one point?

251
00:21:24,647 --> 00:21:25,541
当然
Of course.

252
00:21:25,542 --> 00:21:28,814
对这种疾病 您知道多少?
This disease, do you know what it was?

253
00:21:28,894 --> 00:21:31,635
所有症状都显示这是一种热病
All the signs point to that class of fevers,

254
00:21:31,714 --> 00:21:35,916
其中苏门答腊洪水热是最致命的
of which the Sumatran River Fever is the most deadly.

255
00:21:35,997 --> 00:21:38,286
但并不一定就是这种病
It was not necessarily that however.

256
00:21:38,364 --> 00:21:40,441
那也非常接近
Something very like it.

257
00:21:40,523 --> 00:21:42,506
我已经建议这个可怜人的尸体
I have advised that the poor fellow's body

258
00:21:42,577 --> 00:21:45,175
必须格外小心地来处理
is handled with extreme care.

259
00:21:45,258 --> 00:21:48,356
这种疾病是通过皮肤 表面的创口来传播的
It is a disease transmitted through broken skin you see.

260
00:21:48,426 --> 00:21:50,422
他们必须最最小心
They cannot be too careful.

261
00:21:52,186 --> 00:21:55,346
Savage怎么会染上这种病?
How did Savage come by such a thing?

262
00:21:55,347 --> 00:21:59,307
噢 您可以对此保持谨慎的态度么?
Ah, I can rely on your discretion?

263
00:21:59,308 --> 00:22:00,393
当然
Of course.

264
00:22:00,393 --> 00:22:04,429
我知道他有时 经常呃
I understand Savage sometimes frequented,

265
00:22:04,510 --> 00:22:06,907
或者这么说 有些事使他必须去
well let's to say his affairs took him

266
00:22:06,982 --> 00:22:08,371
Rotherhithe的某个地方
to a part in Rotherhithe

267
00:22:08,445 --> 00:22:10,985
那里主要住的都是中国和印度的水手
inhabited mostly by Chinese and Lascars.

268
00:22:11,056 --> 00:22:13,382
他肯定是在那里染上这种病的
He must have picked it up there.

269
00:22:13,458 --> 00:22:16,320
应该通知Rotherhithe官方这件事
The authorities in Rotherhithe must be informed.

270
00:22:16,321 --> 00:22:17,315
他们会知道的
They will be.

271
00:22:17,316 --> 00:22:18,573
但他们会不会采取适当措施
Whether the measures they take

272
00:22:18,645 --> 00:22:20,762
那就另当别论了
turn out to be appropriate is another matter.

273
00:22:20,763 --> 00:22:22,088
恐怕在大多数机构中的懒惰
Most institutions I'm afraid

274
00:22:22,162 --> 00:22:23,930
都可以够得上判刑了
are run by the criminally lazy.

275
00:22:24,007 --> 00:22:27,449
我认识Penrose Fisher和几个主管
I know Penrose Fisher and the director a little,

276
00:22:27,524 --> 00:22:28,877
我会尽我所能去做的
I'll do what I can.

277
00:22:28,951 --> 00:22:31,170
很感激您的关心 福尔摩斯先生
I'm grateful for you interest, Mr. Holmes.

278
00:22:31,249 --> 00:22:32,495
可怜的Adelaide
Poor Adelaide,

279
00:22:32,572 --> 00:22:34,589
这打击太沉重了
this will hit her very hard.

280
00:23:10,026 --> 00:23:12,111
(寄生虫热病病理)
<i>PATHOLOGY OF PABASITIC FEVERS</i>

281
00:23:23,322 --> 00:23:24,723
(金融家英年早逝--热病死亡之谜)
<i>UNTIMELY DEATH OF FINANCIER</i>

282
00:23:26,467 --> 00:23:28,059
离开Somerleigh?
Leave Somerleigh?

283
00:23:29,774 --> 00:23:31,886
我必须离开Somerleigh么?
I must leave Somerleigh?

284
00:23:31,967 --> 00:23:33,426
一旦遗嘱被确认
As soon as will is proved,

285
00:23:33,499 --> 00:23:37,320
Culverton Smith就有权要求你离开
Culverton Smith is within his rights to ask you to go.

286
00:23:37,398 --> 00:23:39,831
我很抱歉 Adelaide
I'm very sorry, Adelaide.

287
00:23:39,905 --> 00:23:43,513
所有这些都是按照Bernard爵士的遗嘱
All this has its origins in Sir Bernard's will.

288
00:23:43,596 --> 00:23:44,949
我也有部分责任
And partly I blame myself.

289
00:23:45,023 --> 00:23:47,657
继承人限于Victor最年长的表兄
This entailment to Victor's oldest cousin of the house

290
00:23:47,739 --> 00:23:48,878
继承房屋和其余的...
and the rest of it is...

291
00:23:48,957 --> 00:23:51,663
其余的什么?
The rest of it?

292
00:23:51,743 --> 00:23:54,935
从伯克郡产业取得的收入
The income from the Berkshire estate.

293
00:23:55,015 --> 00:23:57,249
那也要归他么?
That will go to him, too?

294
00:23:57,249 --> 00:23:58,697
是的
Yes.

295
00:23:59,123 --> 00:24:02,803
天啊 那还能剩下什么?
Dear God, what is left?

296
00:24:03,266 --> 00:24:05,414
足够你个人
Enough for you to live,

297
00:24:05,496 --> 00:24:08,166
适度而体面的生活
modestly and respectably.

298
00:24:08,246 --> 00:24:10,786
当然 现在这种生活不能继续了
You will not be able to continue as you have done.

299
00:24:10,856 --> 00:24:14,703
我明白了
No, I see.

300
00:24:15,521 --> 00:24:18,969
要我说 我曾经多次要Victor修改
As I say, I had asked Victor many times

301
00:24:18,970 --> 00:24:20,479
遗嘱里限定继承人的范围
to change the terms of the entail

302
00:24:20,480 --> 00:24:22,024
这样可以让你舒服地过一辈子
to favor you in your lifetime.

303
00:24:22,101 --> 00:24:24,154
同时也是完全合法的
It would have been legal of course,

304
00:24:24,225 --> 00:24:28,117
这很容易做 但...
easily done but,

305
00:24:28,194 --> 00:24:29,689
Victor太年轻了
Victor was young.

306
00:24:29,761 --> 00:24:31,814
当然 Culverton Smith
Surely, Culverton Smith

307
00:24:31,885 --> 00:24:34,841
不会行使他的权利去驱逐Savage夫人吧
will not exercise his right to evict Mrs. Savage?

308
00:24:34,913 --> 00:24:36,337
他会的
He might.

309
00:24:36,411 --> 00:24:37,479
为什么你这么想?
Why do you think that?

310
00:24:37,560 --> 00:24:38,805
他一直在接触这件事
He's been in touch.

311
00:24:38,883 --> 00:24:41,280
似乎也知道主要的遗产如何处理
He seems to know the main dispositions of the will.

312
00:24:41,354 --> 00:24:42,908
他说过对产业的收入
He talked of the estate income

313
00:24:42,991 --> 00:24:44,486
要进行恰当的使用
being put to a proper use,

314
00:24:44,558 --> 00:24:46,611
不知道具体是指什么
whatever that meant.

315
00:24:46,681 --> 00:24:47,998
他似乎认为Adelaide
He seemed to think that Adelaide

316
00:24:48,074 --> 00:24:50,577
可以去依靠她的娘家
would be able to rely on her family.

317
00:24:50,650 --> 00:24:52,240
他们也没有办法
They have no means.

318
00:24:52,322 --> 00:24:54,388
当他知道了他就会宽容的
When he knows that he must relent.

319
00:24:54,388 --> 00:24:56,347
我很怀疑
I doubt it.

320
00:24:56,430 --> 00:24:58,091
自从进入我们的生活
He's wanted something like this to happen

321
00:24:58,170 --> 00:25:01,232
他就处心积虑要这样
ever since he came into our lives.

322
00:25:01,303 --> 00:25:04,045
他总是利用Victor的弱点
He encouraged all that was weakest in Victor

323
00:25:04,124 --> 00:25:07,601
希望发生什么不幸
in the hope of some disaster.

324
00:25:07,675 --> 00:25:12,019
他现在得偿所愿了
This is a triumph for him.

325
00:25:12,097 --> 00:25:15,918
或许值得和他谈谈 Adelaide
It may be worth talking to him, Adelaide.

326
00:25:15,996 --> 00:25:18,285
我也觉得是
I suppose so.

327
00:25:18,363 --> 00:25:22,715
如果你肯亲自去求他
If you could bring yourself to plead with him.

328
00:25:25,813 --> 00:25:29,067
为了孩子 我会那么做的
For the children I will do even that.

329
00:25:32,290 --> 00:25:34,961
Percy 快擦擦鼻子
Oh, Percy, do blow your nose.

330
00:25:35,040 --> 00:25:38,412
现在记住这些都发生在9天前
Now remember all this happened nine days ago.

331
00:25:38,486 --> 00:25:40,148
那一天是
That was the day when

332
00:25:40,228 --> 00:25:44,120
女王招待苏丹的Kallipur
the Queen entertained the Sultan of Kallipur

333
00:25:44,197 --> 00:25:47,187
也是Frivolous赢得Birkenhead奖金的那一天
and Frivolous won the Birkenhead Stakes.

334
00:25:47,260 --> 00:25:49,593
-是在Goodwood赢的 -没错
-At Goodwood. -Right.

335
00:25:51,473 --> 00:25:54,986
Harry 你的靴子呢?
Harry, where are your boots?

336
00:25:55,058 --> 00:25:56,090
我知道了
Oh I see.

337
00:25:56,173 --> 00:25:58,250
那就快去Rotherhithe吧
Well then off to Rotherhithe.

338
00:26:00,142 --> 00:26:01,455
祝你们好运
Good luck,

339
00:26:01,456 --> 00:26:02,835
祝你们好运
good luck.

340
00:26:26,636 --> 00:26:28,190
这个 福尔摩斯
There Holmes,

341
00:26:28,273 --> 00:26:29,970
是一份在皮肤表面找到的
that is a list of every blemish

342
00:26:30,049 --> 00:26:31,888
全部斑点的清单
I could find on the skin's surface.

343
00:26:31,963 --> 00:26:34,111
我猜你要寻找传播途径吧
I presume you're seeking the means of transmission?

344
00:26:34,192 --> 00:26:35,925
是的
Yes.

345
00:26:36,002 --> 00:26:37,627
通过皮肤表面的创口
Through broken skin.

346
00:26:37,709 --> 00:26:42,302
Culverton Smith也认为是这么传播的
That is how Culverton Smith believes it was transmitted.

347
00:26:42,373 --> 00:26:45,779
他的意见当然值得参考
Well his opinion is worth knowing certainly.

348
00:26:49,093 --> 00:26:52,736
Fisher 你觉得这个人怎么样?
What do you think of him, Fisher?

349
00:26:52,818 --> 00:26:54,171
他是你朋友么?
He is a friend of yours?

350
00:26:54,246 --> 00:26:56,358
当然不 我并不了解他
Not at all, I hardly know him.

351
00:26:56,439 --> 00:27:01,199
只是读了他的一些论文 仅此而已
I have read a couple of his papers, that's all.

352
00:27:01,278 --> 00:27:02,975
我认为他的工作
Well I think his work,

353
00:27:03,054 --> 00:27:05,628
至少有些部分是很杰出的
in parts, brilliant.

354
00:27:08,067 --> 00:27:09,708
要说有什么缺点的话
If he has a fault it is

355
00:27:09,708 --> 00:27:12,115
那就是不能接受任何的批评
that he can accept no criticism whatsoever.

356
00:27:13,533 --> 00:27:15,419
我确实发现了一个昆虫叮咬点
I did find an insect bite

357
00:27:15,420 --> 00:27:17,635
但皮肤上再没有其他叮咬的痕迹了
but no other punctures of skin at all.

358
00:27:17,711 --> 00:27:19,621
我甚至检查了他的口腔
I even looked inside the mouth.

359
00:27:19,696 --> 00:27:22,665
显然没有任何人为的迹象
It seems clear that no human agency was involved.

360
00:27:23,630 --> 00:27:24,875
我猜你是在调查
I assume you're investigating

361
00:27:24,953 --> 00:27:26,411
这种疾病被什么人
the possibility of this disease

362
00:27:26,484 --> 00:27:29,191
蓄意传播的可能性
having been passed on deliberately.

363
00:27:29,270 --> 00:27:31,144
和你这样思维严密的人会面
Well what a unique delight

364
00:27:31,219 --> 00:27:35,111
真是格外令人愉快
to meet a man with a mind as logical as yours?

365
00:27:39,819 --> 00:27:40,791
是他么?
Is this him?

366
00:27:40,864 --> 00:27:42,632
是的 福尔摩斯先生?
Uh, yes, Mr. Holmes?

367
00:27:42,709 --> 00:27:44,619
噢 好小子
Ah, bravo Ben.

368
00:27:44,693 --> 00:27:45,939
你是?
You are?

369
00:27:46,015 --> 00:27:47,368
Gedgrave
Gedgrave,

370
00:27:47,443 --> 00:27:48,902
John Gedgrave
John Gedgrave.

371
00:27:48,975 --> 00:27:50,505
我是福尔摩斯
Holmes.

372
00:27:52,665 --> 00:27:53,860
这边走
This way.

